Arcane Fire								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:HighArcana.Supernatural.SpecialAttack	VISIBLE:YES	PRECLASS:1,Archmage=1	PRESPELLTYPE:1,Arcane=9					DESC:You change arcane spell energy into arcane fire, manifesting it as a bolt of raw magical energy.																								BONUS:SPELLCAST|TYPE=Arcane;LEVEL=9|-1																			SOURCEPAGE:PrestigeClasses.rtf	BENEFIT:The archmage gains the ability to change arcane spell energy into arcane fire, manifesting it as a bolt of raw magical energy. The bolt is a ranged touch attack with long range (400 feet + 40 feet/level of archmage) that deals 1d6 points of damage per class level of the archmage plus 1d6 points of damage per level of the spell used to create the effect. This ability costs one 9th-level spell slot.
Arcane Reach							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:HighArcana.Supernatural.SpecialAttack	VISIBLE:YES	PRECLASS:1,Archmage=1	PRESPELLTYPE:1,Arcane=7	DEFINE:ArcaneReach|0	DESC:You can use spells with a range of touch on a target up to %1 feet away.|ArcaneReach															STACK:YES	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=2|NOCHOICE			BONUS:SPELLCAST|TYPE=Arcane;LEVEL=7|-1	BONUS:VAR|ArcaneReach|30*count("ABILITIES","CATEGORY=Special Ability","NAME=Arcane Reach")|TYPE=ArcaneReach	SOURCEPAGE:PrestigeClasses.rtf	BENEFIT:The archmage can use spells with a range of touch on a target up to 30 feet away. The archmage must make a ranged touch attack. Arcane reach can be selected a second time as a special ability, in which case the range increases to 60 feet. This ability costs one 7th-level spell slot.
Mastery of Counterspelling					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:HighArcana.SpecialQuality			VISIBLE:YES	PRECLASS:1,Archmage=1	PRESPELLTYPE:1,Arcane=7					DESC:When you counterspell a spell, it is turned back upon the caster as if it were fully affected by a spell turning spell.																				BONUS:SPELLCAST|TYPE=Arcane;LEVEL=7|-1																			SOURCEPAGE:PrestigeClasses.rtf	BENEFIT:When the archmage counterspells a spell, it is turned back upon the caster as if it were fully affected by a spell turning spell. If the spell cannot be affected by spell turning, then it is merely counterspelled. This ability costs one 7th-level spell slot.
Mastery of Elements						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:HighArcana.SpecialQuality			VISIBLE:YES	PRECLASS:1,Archmage=1	PRESPELLTYPE:1,Arcane=8					DESC:You can alter an arcane spell when cast so that it utilizes a different element from the one it normally uses.																					BONUS:SPELLCAST|TYPE=Arcane;LEVEL=8|-1																			SOURCEPAGE:PrestigeClasses.rtf	BENEFIT:The archmage can alter an arcane spell when cast so that it utilizes a different element from the one it normally uses. This ability can only alter a spell with the acid, cold, fire, electricity, or sonic descriptor. The spell's casting time is unaffected. The caster decides whether to alter the spell's energy type and chooses the new energy type when he begins casting. This ability costs one 8th-level spell slot.
Mastery of Shaping						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:HighArcana.SpecialQuality			VISIBLE:YES	PRECLASS:1,Archmage=1	PRESPELLTYPE:1,Arcane=6					DESC:You can alter area and effect spells that use one of the following shapes: burst, cone, cylinder, emanation, or spread.																				BONUS:SPELLCAST|TYPE=Arcane;LEVEL=6|-1																			SOURCEPAGE:PrestigeClasses.rtf	BENEFIT:The archmage can alter area and effect spells that use one of the following shapes: burst, cone, cylinder, emanation, or spread. The alteration consists of creating spaces within the spell's area or effect that are not subject to the spell. The minimum dimension for these spaces is a 5-foot cube. Furthermore, any shapeable spells have a minimum dimension of 5 feet instead of 10 feet. This ability costs one 6th-level spell slot.
Archmage Spell Power		OUTPUTNAME:Spell Power	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:HighArcana.SpecialQuality			VISIBLE:YES	PRECLASS:1,Archmage=1	PRESPELLTYPE:1,Arcane=5					DESC:Your effective caster level increases by +1 (for purposes of determining level-dependent spell variables such as damage dice or range, and caster level checks only).												BONUS:SPELLCAST|TYPE=Arcane;LEVEL=5|-1																			SOURCEPAGE:PrestigeClasses.rtf	BENEFIT:This ability increases the archmage's effective caster level by +1 (for purposes of determining level-dependent spell variables such as damage dice or range, and caster level checks only). This ability costs one 5th-level spell slot.
#Needs alot of work -- Needs a way to dynamicly select a spell from spelllist and then get the level and class of the spell for removal of the spell slot
Spell-Like Ability						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:HighArcana.SpellLike.SpecialAttack		VISIBLE:YES	PRECLASS:1,Archmage=1	PRESPELLTYPE:1,Arcane=5	DEFINE:ArchmageSLA|0	DESC:You permanently prepare the selected arcane spells as spell-like abilities that can be used twice per day.											STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:SPELLS|SPELLTYPE=Arcane[KNOWN=YES]	BONUS:SPELLCAST|TYPE=Arcane;LEVEL=5|-1	BONUS:VAR|ArchmageSLA|1															SOURCEPAGE:PrestigeClasses.rtf	BENEFIT:An archmage who selects this type of high arcana can use one of her arcane spell slots (other than a slot expended to learn this or any other type of high arcana) to permanently prepare one of her arcane spells as a spell-like ability that can be used twice per day. The archmage does not use any components when casting the spell, although a spell that costs XP to cast still does so and a spell with a costly material component instead costs her 10 times that amount in XP. This ability costs one 5th-level spell slot. The spell-like ability normally uses a spell slot of the spell's level, although the archmage can choose to make a spell modified by a metamagic feat into a spell-like ability at the appropriate spell level. The archmage may use an available higher-level spell slot in order to use the spell-like ability more often. Using a slot three levels higher than the chosen spell allows her to use the spell-like ability four times per day, and a slot six levels higher lets her use it six times per day. If spell-like ability is selected more than one time as a high arcana choice, this ability can apply to the same spell chosen the first time (increasing the number of times per day it can be used) or to a different spell.


